{{Infobox dot-com company |name = Care2 |logo = Care2 Logo.png |screenshot = |caption = |company_type = [[Private company|Private]] |founded = {{start date and age|1998}} |location = [[Redwood City, California]] |country = United States |area served = Worldwide |founder = {{Plainlist| *Randy Paynter *Matthew McGlynn *Camilla Eriksson }} |CEO = Randy Paynter |key people = {{Plainlist| *Matthew McGlynn ([[Chief technology officer|CTO]]) *Marlin Miller ([[Chief operating officer|COO]]) }} |products = {{Plainlist| *care2.com *thepetitionsite.com }} |international = Yes |owner = Care2.com, Inc. |employees = >50 |url = {{URL|http://www.care2.com/}} |alexa = {{increase}} 15,876 ({{as of|2018|01|21|alt=January 2018}})<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.alexa.com/siteinfo/care2.com |title=Care2 Alexa Ranking | publisher=Alexa Internet|accessdate=August 14, 2016}}</ref> |type = [[Social networking]], [[Internet petitions|petitioning site]] |registration = Optional <small>(required for creating petitions)</small> |users = 40 million <ref>http://www.care2.com/</ref> |language = English |launched = 1998 |current status = Active }}
'''Care2''' is a [[social network services|social networking]] website that was founded by Randy Paynter in 1998. The goal of the site is to connect activists from around the world with other individuals, organizations and responsible businesses making an impact.<ref>{{cite web | first = Lee | last = Roberts | url=https://www.nytimes.com/2007/03/07/business/businessspecial2/07sustain.html | title=Spreading Their Gospel on the Web | publisher=[[The New York Times]] | website=nytimes.com | date=March 7, 2007}}</ref>
==Overview== Care2 members create an [[online identity]] by filling out a [[User profile|profile]] with personal information, as in most social networking sites, but Care2 also asks for more information about its members' personal lives and involvement in [[activism]]. The social interactions on Care2 revolve around groups that connect people who care about similar political and environmental issues. Members also often participate in [[internet petitions]] and news articles posted by others.
==History== Care2 has been used throughout the years to combat, through petitions, political, environmental and civil rights issues. Recently, Care2 was used by [[Broadway theatre]] playwrights and actors to petition Indiana's [[Indiana SB 101|Religious Freedom Restoration Act]].<ref>{{cite web | first = Mark | last = Kennedy | url=http://abcnews.go.com/Entertainment/wireStory/broadway-takes-aim-contested-indiana-law-petition-30086493 | title=Broadway Takes Aim at Contested Indiana Law With a Petition | publisher=[[ABC News]] | website=abcnews.go.com| date=Apr 2, 2015|accessdate=Apr 3, 2015}}</ref> Care2 is regularly used to promote Boycott, Divestment and Sanctions campaign against Israel.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.care2.com/news/member/124335883/3899433 | title=Reviewing Trashy Hasbara Against BDS| date=Aug 3, 2015}}</ref>
==Security breach== On December 28, 2011, hackers attacked, breached and accessed unencrypted password data on Care2 servers.<ref>{{cite web | first = Randy | last = Paynter | url=http://www.care2.com/care2blog/to-all-care2-members-security-breach.html | title=To All Care2 Members – Security Breach | publisher=Care2 | website=care2.com| date=December 28, 2011}}</ref>
