[[Colonel]] '''Alfredo Enrique Peralta Azurdia''' (June 17, 1908 – February 18, 1997) was [[President of Guatemala]] from March 31, 1963 to July 1, 1966.

Enrique Peralta was born on June 17, 1908 in [[Guatemala City]].  He took over the presidency after a coup against president [[Miguel Ydígoras Fuentes]], under whom he served as Agriculture (1959-1960) and Defense Minister (1961-1963). He set up the [[Institutional Democratic Party]], a pro-military governing party modeled on the [[Institutional Revolutionary Party]], which dominated Guatemalan politics until 1982.<ref>[http://www1.umn.edu/humanrts/ins/guatemala_demochumrts_97.html Guatemala: Democracy and Human Rights (June 1997)]</ref> In the [[Guatemalan general election, 1978|1978 election]], he was the candidate of the [[National Liberation Movement (Guatemala)|National Liberation Movement]] but was defeated by [[Fernando Romeo Lucas García]].

